# Emergent Gravity — Revised Thesis (Scientific Core)

## Introduction / Uvod

This document presents a revised thesis on gravity as an emergent, low-energy effect, incorporating corrections suggested by a physicist to make the idea operational and testable. The corrections ensure universality, isotropy, and compatibility with experimental constraints.  

Ovaj dokument predstavlja revidiranu tezu o gravitaciji kao emergentnom, niskoenergetskom efektu, uzimajući u obzir korekcije koje je predložio fizičar kako bi ideja bila operativna i testabilna. Korekcije osiguravaju univerzalnost, izotropnost i kompatibilnost s eksperimentalnim ograničenjima.


## Key Assumptions / Ključne pretpostavke

1. Gravity is an emergent phenomenon arising from vacuum fluctuations introducing microscopic, random metric noise.  
   Gravitacija je emergentni fenomen koji proizlazi iz fluktuacija vakuuma, uvodeći mikroskopske, nasumične fluktuacije metrike.

2. Effects must be universal: only depend on mass \(m\) and trajectory geometry \(\Delta x\), not material, chemistry, or polarizability.  
   Učinci moraju biti univerzalni: ovise samo o masi \(m\) i geometriji putanje \(\Delta x\), a ne o materijalu, kemiji ili polarizabilnosti.

3. Background noise must be isotropic and have zero mean (\(\langle \phi \rangle = 0\)), respecting Lorentz invariance.  
   Pozadinska buka mora biti izotropna i imati nultu srednju vrijednost (\(\langle \phi \rangle = 0\)), u skladu s Lorentzovom invariancijom.

4. Replace the concept of a frequency-dependent gravitational constant \(G(\omega)\) with a stochastic metric description \(S_\phi(\omega)\).  
   Zamijeniti koncept frekvencijski ovisite gravitacijske konstante \(G(\omega)\) stohastičkim opisom metrike \(S_\phi(\omega)\).


## Corrected Thesis Statement / Revidirana teza

The observable effect in interferometers scales as:

\[
\Delta \Phi \propto m^2 (\Delta x)^2 S_\phi(\omega)
\]

where:  
- \(m\) is the particle mass / masa čestice  
- \(\Delta x\) is the arm separation / udaljenost između “ruku” interferometra  
- \(S_\phi(\omega)\) is the spectrum of universal gravitational phase noise / spektar univerzalne gravitacijske fazne buke

Observable deviations from this scaling would falsify the model.  
Učinci koji odstupaju od ovog skaliranja pobijaju model.


## Intuition: Flags in the Wind / Intuicija: Zastavice na vjetru

- Place two flags close (\(A\), \(\Delta x \sim 0.3\,\mathrm{m}\)) and two flags far apart (\(B\), \(\Delta x \sim 5\,\mathrm{m}\)).  
- Observation: nearby flags move similarly; distant flags move more independently.  
- Analogy: interferometer arms separated by \(\Delta x\) detect weak, correlated noise more sensitively when further apart.

- Postavite dvije zastavice blizu (\(A\), \(\Delta x \sim 0.3\,\mathrm{m}\)) i dvije dalje (\(B\), \(\Delta x \sim 5\,\mathrm{m}\)).  
- Promatranje: bliske zastavice se kreću slično; udaljene se kreću neovisnije.  
- Analogija: ruke interferometra razdvojene \(\Delta x\) osjetljivije detektiraju slabu, koreliranu buku kada su dalje.


## Proposed Experimental Test / Predloženi eksperimentalni test

1. Use a matter-wave interferometer with two geometries (small \(\Delta x\), long time; large \(\Delta x\), short time).  
2. Equalize classical decoherence (residual gas, light, vibrations) in both setups.  
3. Measure phase difference \(\Delta \Phi\) and report as an upper bound on \(S_\phi(\omega)\).  
4. Test different particle masses \(m\) to check \(m^2\) scaling.  

1. Koristite interferometar s valovima tvari s dvije geometrije (mala \(\Delta x\), dugo vrijeme; velika \(\Delta x\), kratko vrijeme).  
2. Izjednačite klasičnu dekoherenciju (ostatni plin, svjetlo, vibracije) u oba eksperimenta.  
3. Mjerite faznu razliku \(\Delta \Phi\) i izvijestite kao gornju granicu za \(S_\phi(\omega)\).  
4. Testirajte različite mase čestica \(m\) kako biste provjerili skaliranje \(m^2\).


## Falsification Criteria / Kriteriji za odbacivanje

- Any dependence on material or chemistry.  
- Scaling not following \(m^2 (\Delta x)^2\) after classical noise correction.  
- Required \(G(\omega)\) dispersion incompatible with astrophysical data.  

- Bilo kakva ovisnost o materijalu ili kemiji.  
- Skaliranje koje ne slijedi \(m^2 (\Delta x)^2\) nakon korekcije klasične buke.  
- Potrebna disperzija \(G(\omega)\) nespojiva s astrofizičkim podacima.


## References / Literatura

1. Bassi, A., Lochan, K., Satin, S., Singh, T. P., & Ulbricht, H. (2013). Models of wave-function collapse, underlying theories, and experimental tests. *Rev. Mod. Phys.*, 85, 471–527.  
2. Pikovski, I., Zych, M., Costa, F., & Brukner, Č. (2015). Universal decoherence due to gravitational time dilation. *Nature Physics*, 11, 668–672.  
3. Milburn, G. J. (1991). Intrinsic decoherence in quantum mechanics. *Phys. Rev. A*, 44, 5401.  



## *Speculative / Hypothetical Interpretations* *(Hipotetski, spekulativni dio)*

> *Note / Napomena:* The following section is **speculative and not experimentally validated**. It is intended for conceptual discussion only.  
> *Sljedeći dio je spekulativan i ne smatra se eksperimentalno potvrđenim. Namijenjen je samo konceptualnoj diskusiji.*

* One can imagine an interpretative layer where gravity emerges from collective coherence of quantum fluctuations in a relational field.  
* Formal expression (for conceptual illustration only):

\[
G_{\text{emergent}} \sim \langle \Psi | \hat{R}_{\text{hypothetical}} | \Psi \rangle
\]

* Here \(\hat{R}_{\text{hypothetical}}\) is **not defined in standard physics**; it serves as a metaphor for correlated fluctuations at macroscopic scales.  
* This conceptual layer does **not change the testable predictions** of the core thesis (\(\Delta \Phi \propto m^2 (\Delta x)^2 S_\phi(\omega)\)) but provides a possible narrative for emergent behavior.

* Moguće je zamisliti interpretativni sloj gdje gravitacija proizlazi iz kolektivne koherencije kvantnih fluktuacija u relacijskom polju.  
* Formalni izraz (samo za konceptualnu ilustraciju):

\[
G_{\text{emergent}} \sim \langle \Psi | \hat{R}_{\text{hypothetical}} | \Psi \rangle
\]

* Ovdje \(\hat{R}_{\text{hypothetical}}\) **nije definiran u standardnoj fizici**; služi kao metafora za korelirane fluktuacije na makroskopskim skalama.  
* Ovaj konceptualni sloj **ne mijenja eksperimentalno testabilne predikcije** osnovne teze (\(\Delta \Phi \propto m^2 (\Delta x)^2 S_\phi(\omega)\)), već daje mogući narativ za emergentno ponašanje.
